					<item>
						<guid isPermaLink="false">610-</guid>
						<itunes:image href="http://www.fresnourc.com/podcast_images/itunes_main_feed.png" />
						<title>Ascending Beyond Canaan (LD 18; Psalm 68)</title>
						<pubDate></pubDate>
						<itunes:subtitle>LD 18; Psalm 68 (www.fresnourc.com)</itunes:subtitle>
						<itunes:summary> I know that when I summarize the work of Christ I speak of the life, death, and resurrection of Christ.  I guess that I have indoctrinated myself into think that those three things are the most essential things for the gospel of Christ to be true.  So, I wonder why I and many other Christians do not say, &quot;life, death, resurrection, and ascension of Christ.&quot;  Why is it so easy for Christians to leave out the blessing of the ascension of Christ?   Do we see the ascension of Christ as a blessing?  If you are curious about these questions please stay tuned to our sermon titled, &quot;Ascending Beyond Canaan.&quot;</itunes:summary>
