					<item>
						<guid isPermaLink="false">605-Thu, 31 May 2012 17:12:07 PDT</guid>
						<itunes:image href="http://www.fresnourc.com/podcast_images/itunes_main_feed.png" />
						<title>Why Does the Resurrection Matter? (Psalm 16, LD 17)</title>
						<pubDate>Thu, 31 May 2012 17:12:07 PDT</pubDate>
						<itunes:subtitle>Psalm 16, LD 17 www.fresnourc.com</itunes:subtitle>
						<itunes:summary>Christ&apos;s resurrection from the dead is probably one of the biggest stumbling blocks of Christianity.  You see if we do not talk about the dead being raised then Christianity is more believable.  Why is the bodily resurrection of Christ so essential for our faith?  Is the bodily resurrection of Christ only significant for our faith or is it significant even for the Old Testament saints?  Can we find a hope and assurance of the resurrection even in the Old Testament?  If you are curious about these questions please stay tuned to our sermon titled, &quot;Why Does Christ&apos;s Resurrection Matter?&quot;</itunes:summary>
						<description>Christ&apos;s resurrection from the dead is probably one of the biggest stumbling blocks of Christianity.  You see if we do not talk about the dead being raised then Christianity is more believable.  Why is the bodily resurrection of Christ so essential for our faith?  Is the bodily resurrection of Christ only significant for our faith or is it significant even for the Old Testament saints?  Can we find a hope and assurance of the resurrection even in the Old Testament?  If you are curious about these questions please stay tuned to our sermon titled, &quot;Why Does Christ&apos;s Resurrection Matter?&quot;</description>
