						<itunes:subtitle>John 1:1-18 (www.fresnourc.com)</itunes:subtitle>
						<itunes:summary>You can read in Exodus 25 the call for Israel to offer precious metals, stones, and even material to Moses for the building of the tabernacle.  This is probably something that would be encouraging because now there is a visible meeting with God.  Does this mean that now that we are in a New Testament time that we have an inferior tabernacle?  Where is our tabernacle today?  How can we be assured that God dwells with us?  If you are curious about these questions please stay tuned to our sermon titled, &quot;Our Tabernacle.&quot;</itunes:summary>
