						<itunes:subtitle>LD 27; Colossians 2:11, 12 (www.fresnourc.com)</itunes:subtitle>
						<itunes:summary> It is tempting to think that the application of baptism is only for the people who have claimed Christ.  If we baptize infants we are saying that they claim Christ or maybe that they are starting the road to justification.  However, our church does baptize infants, and so why would we baptize infants?  What basis is there for baptizing infants? If you are curious about these questions please stay tuned to our sermon titled, &quot;Having Been Buried with HIm.&quot; </itunes:summary>
