						<guid isPermaLink="false">599-Tue, 08 May 2012 19:06:27 EDT</guid>
						<itunes:image href="http://www.fresnourc.com/podcast_images/itunes_main_feed.png" />
						<title>God&apos;s Forsaken Son (LD 15; Psalm 22)</title>
						<pubDate>Tue, 08 May 2012 19:06:27 EDT</pubDate>
						<itunes:subtitle>Psalm 22; Lord&apos;s Day 15 (www.fresnourc.com)</itunes:subtitle>
						<itunes:summary> When we think about the work of Christ it is almost cliche among Christians to say that Christ has suffered.  He has suffered, but why is that important?  This is a question that I think we take for granted because if we are honest we expect life to go well for us as we faithfully follow the Lord.  However, how is this expectation for a blessed life working for King David who most likely wrote Psalm 22?  Does his life always go well as he serves the Lord?  If you are curious about these questions please stay tuned to our sermon titled, &quot;God&apos;s Forsaken Son.&quot;</itunes:summary>
