						<guid isPermaLink="false">595-Fri, 27 Apr 2012 14:04:46 EDT</guid>
						<itunes:image href="http://www.fresnourc.com/podcast_images/itunes_main_feed.png" />
						<title>David&apos;s Son (LD 14; Psalm 132)</title>
						<pubDate>Fri, 27 Apr 2012 14:04:46 EDT</pubDate>
						<itunes:subtitle>LD 14; Psalm 132 (www.fresnourc.com)</itunes:subtitle>
						<itunes:summary> I hope that we would all agree that God is Almighty.  If you think about what it means to come before an Almighty God this is something that could be terrifying. This is the God who wiped out nations, and made a little nomadic people great.  So, since this is true, can we come boldly before the throne of God?  On what basis can we come boldly before the throne of God?  Do we have any hints from the Psalms showing us how to be bold before the Lord?  If you are curious about these questions please stay tuned to our sermon titled, &quot;David&apos;s Son.&quot;</itunes:summary>
