					<item>
						<guid isPermaLink="false">594-Sun, 22 Apr 2012 17:19:41 EDT</guid>
						<itunes:image href="http://www.fresnourc.com/podcast_images/itunes_main_feed.png" />
						<title>Independence Day (Joel 3:1-8)</title>
						<pubDate>Sun, 22 Apr 2012 17:19:41 EDT</pubDate>
						<itunes:subtitle>Joel 3:1-8 (www.fresnourc.com)</itunes:subtitle>
						<itunes:summary> Have you ever been cut off in traffic and wondered how someone can get away with such an offense?  Have you ever wished that a police officer would have witnessed the person who aggressively cut you off so you can have the satisfaction of knowing that the person got a ticket?  Imagine how Israel must have felt in her exile as she was being sold as slaves once again.  The Israelites must have wondered if the Lord really cared about them.  They must have wished that the Lord saw such offenses.  So, did the Lord see the offenses? Does the Lord even care about such offenses?  If you are curious about these questions please stay tuned to our sermon titled, &quot;Independence Day.&quot;</itunes:summary>
