						<guid isPermaLink="false">592-Sun, 15 Apr 2012 17:55:06 EDT</guid>
						<itunes:image href="http://www.fresnourc.com/podcast_images/itunes_main_feed.png" />
						<title>The Last Exodus (Joel 2:28-32)</title>
						<pubDate>Sun, 15 Apr 2012 17:55:06 EDT</pubDate>
						<itunes:subtitle>Joel 2:28-32 (www.fresnourc.com)</itunes:subtitle>
						<itunes:summary>We saw in our series on 1 Thessalonians that Paul is encouraging the church to look forward to the day of the Lord.  However, the prophet Joel, who makes the Day of the Lord a major topic in his prophecy, does not seem to present this day as something joyful.  In our study the day of the Lord has been the army that comes against Israel and brings destruction.  Does Joel ever promise relief from this army?  Does Joel present anything good about this day?  If you are curious about these questions please stay tuned to our sermon titled, &quot;The Last Exodus.&quot;</itunes:summary>
